# nlmixr2extra 5.1.0

## Deprecated functions

* `covarSearchAuto()` has been renamed to `runSCM()`. The old name is retained
  as a deprecated alias that forwards all arguments and emits a deprecation
  warning. It will be removed in a future release.

* `bootstrapFit()` has been renamed to `runBootstrap()`. The old name is
  retained as a deprecated alias that forwards all arguments and emits a
  deprecation warning. It will be removed in a future release.

## `runSCM()` — major redesign of stepwise covariate model building

* Function is now exported and part of the public API (previously `@noRd`).

* New `pairsVec` parameter allows explicit specification of
  parameter-covariate pairs to test, bypassing the cartesian product of
  `varsVec × covarsVec`.

* New `shapes` and `customShapes` parameters control which covariate
  relationship shapes are tested. Built-in shapes: `"power"` (default),
  `"lin"`, `"log"`, `"identity"`. User-defined shapes can be supplied as a
  named list of builder functions via `customShapes`.

* New `inits` parameter accepts a named list of initial estimates (and
  optional bounds) per shape, applied globally across all pairs.

* Warm-starting: after each accepted forward step, the estimated theta value
  is automatically used as the starting estimate for subsequent steps.

* New `missingToken` parameter: covariate columns containing `NA` or the
  specified sentinel value now generate `ifelse()` guards in the model
  expression, substituting the population-typical value rather than
  propagating missingness into the objective function.

* New `includedRelations` parameter: pairs specified here are forced into the
  model before backward elimination begins, analogous to PsN's
  `[included_relations]`. Missing pairs are added and the model is re-fit
  once before backward stepping.

* New `data` parameter: an explicit dataset can now be passed instead of
  always relying on `nlme::getData(fit)`.

* New `catCutoff` parameter (default `0.05`): categorical levels with fewer
  than this proportion of subjects are excluded from the candidate set.

* New `outputDir` parameter: cache directory is now auto-derived as
  `<fitname>_scm_<N>` (sequential) when `NULL`. On `restart = TRUE` the
  existing directory is backed up with a timestamp rather than deleted.
  The old scheme used `digest::digest(fit)` hashing; `digest` is no longer
  a hard dependency.

* New `saveModels` parameter (default `TRUE`): set to `FALSE` to run the
  search without writing any files to disk.

* New `verbose` parameter (default `FALSE`): prints the full candidate table
  before each step and the complete results table after fitting.

* New `control` parameter: a control object (e.g. `saemControl()`) passed to
  every internal `nlmixr2()` call. When `NULL` the base fit's control
  settings are inherited.

* New `print` parameter (default `100`): optimiser print frequency, always
  applied as `control$print`.

* New `workers` parameter (default `NULL`): enables parallel fitting of
  candidate models via `future`. A positive integer temporarily sets a
  `multisession` plan for the duration of the search.

* New `confirm` parameter (default `TRUE`): in interactive sessions a
  pre-search summary table is printed and the user is prompted to confirm
  before fitting begins. Set to `FALSE` to suppress the prompt.

## `runBootstrap()` — bootstrap enhancements

* New `outputDir` parameter: cache directory is now auto-derived as
  `<fitName>_boot_<N>` (sequential) when `NULL`, rather than being
  hard-coded from the fit's MD5 hash.

* New `updateFit` parameter (default `TRUE`): controls whether bootstrap
  results are attached to the original `fit` object as `fit$bootstrap`.
  Set to `FALSE` to leave `fit` completely unchanged.

* New `workers` parameter (default `NULL`): enables parallel fitting of
  bootstrap replicates via `future`/`future.apply`.

* Return value changed: `runBootstrap()` now returns a named list with
  elements `seed`, `results`, `summary`, `model`, `outputDir`, and
  `timestamp`, in addition to (when `updateFit = TRUE`) attaching results
  to the fit object as before.

## `runSIR()` — sampling importance resampling

* `runSIR()` and helper functions have been added as of version 5.1.0 to run
  multi-iteration sampling importance resampling for nlmixr2 fits.

* `runSIR()` parallel OFV evaluation via `future` is now documented, tested,
  and no longer depends on `progressr` being installed.

## Other changes

* `future` and `future.apply` promoted from Suggests to Imports to support
  the new parallel execution features in `runSCM()`, `runBootstrap()`, and
  `runSIR()`.

* `progressr` is now used only as optional progress-reporting support for
  future-backed parallel helpers.

* Non-ASCII box-drawing characters in `R/computingutil.R` replaced with
  ASCII hyphens (CRAN compliance).

* Duplicate `@param` roxygen entries in `runBootstrap()` documentation
  removed; previously undocumented parameters `outputDir`, `updateFit`, and
  `workers` now fully documented. This resolves an `R CMD check` WARNING.

* New integration test scripts added in `inst/scripts/`:
  `warfarin_scm_test.R`, `warfarin_scm_external_test.R`, and
  `warfarin_scm_test_tmp.R`.

* New unit test file `tests/testthat/test-scm.R` with 50+ cases covering
  `.parseInitSpec`, `.buildPairs`, `.enrichPairs`, `.expandShapes`, and
  forward/backward search logic.

# nlmixr2extra 3.0.3

* Allow raw fits to be returned (or only the parameters)

# nlmixr2extra 3.0.2

* Make sure bootstrapped thetas are named.  Fixed issue #76

# nlmixr2extra 3.0.1

* Remove non-functioning SCM for now (#71)

# nlmixr2extra 3.0.0

* New `profile()` method for likelihood profiling (Issue #1)

# nlmixr2extra 2.0.10

* `bootstrapFit()` fixes `se` option (Issue #66)

# nlmixr2extra 2.0.9

* `bootstrapFit()` now will be more careful handling `NA` values so
  they do not completely affect results (Issue #59)

* `bootstrapFit()` will now only take the correlation of the non-zero
  diagonals (Issue #59).

* New method for `knit_print()` will generate model equations for LaTeX
  reporting automatically.

* Tests are now skipped if they contain linear compartment models that
  need gradients when the gradients are not compiled (as in the case
  of intel c++).

# nlmixr2extra 2.0.8

* Use `assignInMyNamespace()` instead of using the global assignment
  operator for the horseshoe prior

* Be specific in version requirements (as requested by CRAN checks)

* Move the `theoFitOde.rda` data build to `devtools::document()` to
  reduce CRAN build time (could add more standard models like warfarin
  for package developers which takes way too much time for CRAN)

# nlmixr2extra 2.0.7

* Fix `cli` issues with the new `cli` 3.4+ release that will allow
  bootstrapping to run again (before `cli` would error, this fixes the
  `donttest` issues on CRAN).

* Fixed step-wise covariate selection to work a bit better with the
  updated UI, thanks to Vishal Sarsani

* Added lasso covariate selection (thanks to Vishal Sarsani)

* Added horseshoe prior covarite selecion (thanks to Vishal Sarsani)

* Added a `NEWS.md` file to track changes to the package.
